Professor Jay Berzofsky of the U.S. National Cancer Institute in Bethesday, Maryland, said: "Our findings suggest that the vaccine is extremely effective."
HER2 "allows various types of cancer to stop growing," including breast, ovarian, lung, and colon cancer, said Professor Berzofsky.
A similar method in which immune cells are removed from patients and they are 'known' to attack cancer cells has worked in the treatment of one type of leukemia.
