HIV infection caused by sex is a serious problem within the Chinese LGBT community.
Homosexuality has not been illegal in China since 1997, but major discrimination against LGBT people is still reportedly occurring.
Due to conservative values in the country, research has estimated that 70-90% of men who have sex with other men eventually marry a woman.
